brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of this study is to determine the intra- and interobserver agreement.

clinical_study.brief_title: Intra- and Interobserver Agreement in the Assessment of Human Embryos
clinical_study.condition: the Focus of This Study is to Measure the Intra- and Interobserver Agreement for the Evaluation of Early Stage Embryos

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  fertilized embryos

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  unfertilized embryos

facility.name: University Hospital Leuven, Catholic University Leuven

clinical_study.official_title: Intra-and Inter-observer Agreement in the Morphological Assessment of Human Embryos

oversight_info.authority: Belgium: Federale Commissie voor medisch en wetenschappelijk onderzoek op embryo's in vitro

primary_outcome.description: Variation in observer assessment of embryo characteristics on day 1, 2 and 3 of embryo development. Assessment of these characteristics is standard procedure. Safety and tolerability or efficacy issues are not relevant for this outcome.
primary_outcome.measure: Evaluation of the intra- and inter-observer variability in the assessement of human embryos
